  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a HarfBuzz color value (<c>hb_color_t</c>) packed as <c>0xBBGGRRAA</c> (blue in the high byte, alpha in the low byte).</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`HBColor` is a thin wrapper around the native HarfBuzz `hb_color_t` type, which stores BGRA
color values in the packed format `0xBBGGRRAA`. This differs from `SKColor`, which uses ARGB
order (`0xAARRGGBB`). Always use the named channel properties (`Red`, `Green`, `Blue`, `Alpha`)
to correctly extract individual components rather than reading raw byte offsets.

`HBColor` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from individual channels
var color = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 128, blue: 0, alpha: 255);

// Inspect channels
Console.WriteLine($"R={color.Red} G={color.Green} B={color.Blue} A={color.Alpha}");

// Convert to/from SKColor
SKColor skColor = color.ToSKColor();
HBColor back = skColor.ToHBColor();
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
